### SUMMARY TABLE

| Issue | File | Line(s) | Severity | Impact | Fix |
|-------|------|---------|----------|--------|-----|
| Logging in loops (categories) | FBT service | 266-278 | CRITICAL | 400+ logs/sec per loop | Remove loop logs, log summary after loop |
| Cache hit/miss logging | cache.service | 88, 92 | CRITICAL | 36-72M logs/day | Use debug level OR rate-limit |
| Cache hit/miss (Algolia) | algolia.service | 275, 282 | CRITICAL | High-frequency path | Use debug level OR remove |
| Cache hit/miss (Addons) | addons.service | 76, 83 | CRITICAL | High-frequency path | Use debug level |
| @LogExecution on trivial getters | style-colors, style-alternatives, etc | Multiple | HIGH | Overhead on every request | Remove @LogExecution from simple getters |
| Email recommendations per-type logging | email-recommendations.service | 162-195 | MEDIUM | 3+ logs per request × volume | Reduce logging overhead |
| Trending products multiple logs | trending-products.service | 62-101 | MEDIUM | Multiple logs per request | Consolidate logs |

---

### RECOMMENDED ACTIONS

1. **Change cache `.log()` to `.debug()`** on lines 88 and 92 of cache.service.ts (and algolia.service, addons.service)
2. **Remove logging from the loop** in `selectRandomStylesFromCategoriesGeneric` (FBT lines 266-278) - log summary after loop instead
3. **Remove @LogExecution from trivial getter methods** in DB services (style-colors, style-alternatives, styles-hash, condensed-features, styles-mv)
4. **Consolidate multiple logs** in hot-path services (trending-products, email-recommendations) - one log per entry/exit instead of multiple intermediate logs
5. **Rate-limit or remove** logging for every loop iteration in color matching logic
